  "body": "I am not sure if this is a concern in terms of security or this is an acceptable behaviour for us. Needs to be discussed. \r\n\r\n**Steps:** \r\n\r\n1. Enable biometrics in app\r\n2. Close the app\r\n3. Reset biometrics settings on the device: i.e. delete current Fingerprint/Face ID and add a new one\r\n4. Open the app and see if you can login via new biometrics\r\n\r\n**Actual result:** App biometry settings are not reset. User is able to login via biometrics despite biometric has been updated on device. \r\n\r\n\r\n**Expected result:** once biometrics settings have been updated on device level - login via biometrics should be reset in app. User should re-enable biometrics to be able to use it. Otherwise, anyone who updates FaceID/fingerprint on the device will be able to enter the App. \r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status version: nightly \r\n- Operating System: Android, iOS\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
